aston.group20.model

Class Simulator

  • java.lang.Object
    • aston.group20.model.Simulator

  • public class Simulator
extends java.lang.Object
    This class models a simplistic Airport simulation, based on an Airport that is managing Incoming and Outgoing Aircraft.
    Version:
    1.0, March 2014
    Author:
    Group_20

    • Constructor Detail

      • Simulator

        public Simulator()
        The constructor creates a Simulator object, which contains an Airport where the majority of the action will take place, as well as a StringBuilder for a longReport. The constructor also calls the reset method in order to ensure that everything is ready for a new Simulation.
        See Also:
        reset()

    • Method Detail

      • main

        public static void main(java.lang.String[] args)
        Creates a GUI which will allow the user to run the Simulation for a specified number of steps, and also allow them to change the various Aircraft probabilities, as well as the Strategy/Seed used.

      • simulate

        public void simulate(int numSteps)
        Run the simulation from its current state for the given number of steps; the simulateOneStep method will be called until the number of steps has been run, after which the state of the object will be finalised and the end report will be printed to the console.
        Parameters:
        numSteps - the number of steps to run the simulation for
        See Also:
        simulateOneStep()

      • simulateOneStep

        public void simulateOneStep()
        Run the simulation from its current state for a single step. This will call the Airport.schedule method which will cause the Aircraft to take the appropriate actions if necessary. This method also has the chance to generate an Aircraft by calling the generateAircraft() method.
        See Also:
        Airport.schedule()

      • generateAircraft

        private void generateAircraft()
        This method has the potential to add an Aircraft to either the Incoming or Outgoing queues of the Airports AirControlTower. It calls the Hangar's generateAircraft method which could return an Aircraft that would then be added to one of the queues.
        See Also:
        Hangar.generateAircraft(Random)

      • reset

        public void reset()
        Resets the simulation so that it is ready to run again if it is required.

      • setProbabilities

        public void setProbabilities(double commercial,
                    double glider,
                    double light)
        This method sets the probabilities for the creation of Aircraft through the Hangar.generateAircraft(Random) method.
        Parameters:
        commercial - the probability of generating a commercial aircraft.
        glider - the probability of generating a glider.
        light - the probability of generating a light aircraft.

      • getStrategies

        public Strategy[] getStrategies()
        This method returns the Strategy Array containing the different types of Strategies that could potentially be used in the Simulation.
        Returns:
        the Strategy Array containing the different types of Strategies.

      • setStrategy

        public void setStrategy(int chosenStrategy)
        This method sets the strategy by using the parameter integer; when the simulate(int) method is called the Strategy is chosen through the strategies array and the chosenStrategy integer.
        Parameters:
        chosenStrategy - the strategy that should be chosen from the strategies array.

      • setSeed

        public void setSeed(int seed)
        This method sets the seed that the random number generator 'rand' should be using. It is called in the reset() method to ensure that the simulation is up to date and accurate.
        Parameters:
        seed - the seed that the random number generator 'rand' should be using.

      • getResults

        public java.lang.String getResults()
        This method returns a String that contains the shorter end results of the Simulation.
        Returns:
        a String containing the end results of the Simulation.

      • printLongReport

        public java.lang.String printLongReport()
        This method returns a String that contains the longer report of the Simulation. It contains information for each step of the simulation, formatted for easy readability.
        Returns:
        a String containing the longer report of the Simulation.

      • getLongReport

        public java.lang.StringBuilder getLongReport()
        This method returns the complete longReport of the Simulation. It contains detailed information from each and every step of the Simulation.
        Returns:
        a StringBuilder which contains the complete longReport of the Simulation.
